  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Greening the Agro-Tourism Business in Romania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to improve wastewater, organic-waste, and manure management systems in rural areas, as well as educate the rural population on the importance of   organic agriculture production.  The wastewater, domestic waste and manure management systems in Romania, especially in rural areas, are characterized by insufficient protection of water resources; a very low percentage of the population being connected to sewage and waste water treatment systems; malfunctioning of the existent treatment stations; and an overall lack of compliance with waste management policies. Manure management systems are rare in Romania. Implementing such systems will prevent groundwater contamination and will promote efficient use of organic fertilizers. The proposed wastewater management systems, using reed-bed filters, will be unique to Romania. The target area chosen for this project is of high cultural and touristic value. Agro-tourism is a well-established local business and brings visitors from all around the country and even abroad. The innovative wastewater system will bring added value to the location, as tourist facilities that care and protect the environment.</narrative>
  </description>
